**NEW: Firebase Push Notifications** (Dec 16, 2025)

Register Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) token for push notifications.

**Access:** All authenticated users (Customer, Technician, Dispatcher, Admin, Call Center)

**Use Cases:**
- Register device for push notifications when app starts
- Update FCM token when it changes (Firebase refreshes tokens periodically)
- Enable real-time job assignment notifications
- Receive order status updates
- Get payment confirmations

**Request Body:**
```json
{
  "fcmToken": "dA1B2c3D4e5F6g7H8i9J0k:APA91bH..._your_firebase_token_here"
}
```

**Success Response (200 OK):**
```json
{
  "message": "FCM token registered successfully",
  "fcmToken": "dA1B2c3D4e5F6g7H8i9J0k:APA91bH..."
}
```

**Error Responses:**
- 400 Bad Request - FCM token is required
- 401 Unauthorized - Invalid or missing JWT token
- 404 Not Found - User not found

**How It Works:**
1. Mobile app obtains FCM token from Firebase SDK
2. App sends token to this endpoint after user login
3. Token stored in User.fcmToken field in database
4. Backend uses token to send push notifications
5. Notifications include sound, vibration, high priority

**Push Notification Types:**
- ðŸ”” **Job Assignment** - Technician receives new work order
- ðŸ“ **Status Updates** - Customer notified of technician arrival
- ðŸ’° **Payment Confirmation** - Payment verified notifications
- âš ï¸ **Important Alerts** - System notifications

**Push Notification Format:**
```json
{
  "notification": {
    "title": "ðŸ”” New Job Assigned!",
    "body": "Work Order WO-001: AC Repair at Customer Location"
  },
  "data": {
    "type": "WO_ASSIGNED",
    "woId": "123",
    "woNumber": "WO-001"
  },
  "android": {
    "priority": "high",
    "notification": {
      "sound": "default",
      "channelId": "job_assignments",
      "vibrate": [200, 100, 200]
    }
  },
  "apns": {
    "payload": {
      "aps": {
        "sound": "default",
        "badge": 1,
        "contentAvailable": true
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**Mobile App Integration:**

**React Native (Firebase):**
```javascript
import messaging from '@react-native-firebase/messaging';
import axios from 'axios';

async function registerForPushNotifications() {
  // Request permission
  const authStatus = await messaging().requestPermission();
  const enabled = authStatus === messaging.AuthorizationStatus.AUTHORIZED;

  if (enabled) {
    // Get FCM token
    const fcmToken = await messaging().getToken();

    // Register with backend
    await axios.post('/api/notifications/fcm-token', {
      fcmToken
    }, {
      headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${jwtToken}` }
    });

    console.log('FCM token registered:', fcmToken);
  }
}

// Handle incoming notifications
messaging().onMessage(async remoteMessage => {
  console.log('Notification received:', remoteMessage);
  // Show notification UI
});

// Handle notification tap
messaging().onNotificationOpenedApp(remoteMessage => {
  console.log('Notification opened:', remoteMessage.data);
  // Navigate to appropriate screen
});
```

**Flutter (firebase_messaging):**
```dart
import 'package:firebase_messaging/firebase_messaging.dart';
import 'package:http/http.dart' as http;

Future<void> registerFCMToken() async {
  FirebaseMessaging messaging = FirebaseMessaging.instance;

  // Request permission
  NotificationSettings settings = await messaging.requestPermission(
    alert: true,
    sound: true,
    badge: true,
  );

  if (settings.authorizationStatus == AuthorizationStatus.authorized) {
    // Get FCM token
    String? fcmToken = await messaging.getToken();

    // Register with backend
    await http.post(
      Uri.parse('$baseUrl/api/notifications/fcm-token'),
      headers: {
        'Authorization': 'Bearer $jwtToken',
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
      },
      body: jsonEncode({'fcmToken': fcmToken}),
    );
  }

  // Listen to messages
  FirebaseMessaging.onMessage.listen((RemoteMessage message) {
    print('Notification: ${message.notification?.title}');
  });
}
```

**Best Practices:**
1. **Register on Login:** Call this endpoint after successful login
2. **Handle Token Refresh:** Firebase refreshes tokens periodically, update when changed
3. **Register on App Start:** If user already logged in, register token on app startup
4. **Handle Errors:** Gracefully handle registration failures
5. **Remove on Logout:** Call DELETE endpoint when user logs out

**Security:**
- JWT authentication required
- Token stored securely in database
- Only the user can register their own token
- Tokens encrypted in transit (HTTPS)

**Related Endpoints:**
- DELETE /api/notifications/fcm-token - Remove token on logout
- GET /api/notifications - Get in-app notifications

**Documentation:**
- Full guide: FIREBASE_PUSH_NOTIFICATIONS.md
- Firebase setup: https://firebase.google.com/docs/cloud-messaging

TESTED & WORKING (Dec 16, 2025)

**Remove FCM token from user account**

Call this endpoint when user logs out to stop receiving push notifications.

**Access:** All authenticated users

**When to Call:**
- User logs out
- User disables push notifications in settings
- App is uninstalled (call in cleanup if possible)
- User switches accounts

**Success Response (200 OK):**
```json
{
  "message": "FCM token removed successfully"
}
```

**What Happens:**
1. FCM token cleared from User.fcmToken field
2. User will no longer receive push notifications
3. Can re-register token by calling POST endpoint again

**Mobile App Integration:**

**React Native:**
```javascript
import axios from 'axios';

async function logout() {
  try {
    // Remove FCM token from backend
    await axios.delete('/api/notifications/fcm-token', {
      headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${jwtToken}` }
    });

    // Clear local auth token
    await AsyncStorage.removeItem('authToken');

    // Navigate to login screen
    navigation.navigate('Login');
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Logout error:', error);
  }
}
```

**Flutter:**
```dart
import 'package:http/http.dart' as http;

Future<void> logout() async {
  try {
    // Remove FCM token
    await http.delete(
      Uri.parse('$baseUrl/api/notifications/fcm-token'),
      headers: {'Authorization': 'Bearer $jwtToken'},
    );

    // Clear local storage
    await storage.delete(key: 'authToken');

    // Navigate to login
    Navigator.pushReplacementNamed(context, '/login');
  } catch (e) {
    print('Logout error: $e');
  }
}
```

**Best Practices:**
1. **Always call on logout** - Prevents notifications to logged-out users
2. **Handle errors gracefully** - Don't block logout if removal fails
3. **Silent failure** - User doesn't need to see errors from this
4. **Clean up locally** - Also delete local FCM token cache

**Error Handling:**
```javascript
async function removeFCMToken() {
  try {
    await axios.delete('/api/notifications/fcm-token', {
      headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${token}` }
    });
  } catch (error) {
    // Log but don't show error to user
    console.log('FCM removal failed:', error);
    // Continue with logout anyway
  }
}
```

**Security:**
- JWT authentication required
- User can only remove their own token
- Safe to call multiple times (idempotent)

TESTED & WORKING (Dec 16, 2025)

